&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3 Rotational Maternity Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are looking for an enthusiastic support worker to join our Maternity team working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The post will be rotational working between community hubs and the hospital to support the Better Births agenda, including weekends, nights &amp; bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Experience in supporting women with infant feeding &amp; providing parent education are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have experience of working in Maternity services and have your care certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; If you are enthusiastic about working within a passionate caring team of midwives and support workers to ensure safe and effective care for women and enjoy the challenge of a busy fast paced ever changing environment, then please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date for application: 18th of November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
